# Web Platform Components

The web platform is the frontend interface for Biasbuster, providing users with interactive bias analysis capabilities.

## Key Pages
- [index.html](mdc:web-platform/index.html) - Main landing page and bias analysis tool
- [ai-literacy.html](mdc:web-platform/ai-literacy.html) - AI Literacy Hub with educational resources
- [ethics-committee.html](mdc:web-platform/ethics-committee.html) - Ethics & AI Committee Portal
- [judge-dashboard.html](mdc:web-platform/judge-dashboard.html) - Dashboard for Startupathon judges

## Core JavaScript
- [script.js](mdc:web-platform/script.js) - Main application logic including:
  - API integration
  - Content analysis
  - Result visualization
  - Mock response generation for offline mode

## Running the Web Platform
The web platform can be started using Python's HTTP server:
```
cd web-platform && python -m http.server 8000
```
Then access the application at http://localhost:8000
